---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 190
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Humility=The Conquest of Pride
  - 423
By: St Louis de Montfort
---
Ah! how many cedars of Lebanon, how many stars of the firmament, have
we not seen fall miserable, and in the twinkling of an eye lose all
their height and their brightness!  Whence comes that sad and curious
change? It was not for want of grace, which is wanting to no man; but
it was for want of humility. They thought themselves capable of
guarding their own treasures. They trusted in themselves, relied upon
themselves.
